# Progress Harness (schema v1)

## Design principle

- **Stable**: PROGRESS.md section headings and status legend.
- **Volatile**: module IDs, feature names, verify script names — live in ARCHITECTURE.md / PRD.md.
- **Never hardcode** M0–M8 or feature lists inside this rule.

## Source of truth

| Topic | File |
|-------|------|
| What to build / user acceptance | PRD.md |
| How work is sliced + verify commands | ARCHITECTURE.md |
| Current pulse + next action | PROGRESS.md |

When modules change: edit ARCHITECTURE first, then sync PROGRESS.

## When to update PROGRESS.md (mandatory)

Same session, if any of: code/config/docs changed; verify passed; git commit; user confirmed/rejected a feature; blocker appears/clears.

Skip only for pure Q&A with zero repo changes.

## Status legend

| Mark | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `[ ]` | Not started |
| `[~]` | Implemented; verify or sign-off pending |
| `[x]` | Verified |
| `[!]` | Blocked — note in Snapshot |

## Minimum update each coding session

1. Snapshot — phase, focus, Git (`git log -1 --oneline`), blockers
2. Work breakdown — rows match ARCHITECTURE module table
3. Requirement traceability — match PRD mapping; update status only
4. Recent changes — one dated line; keep last ~5
5. Next session — one copy-paste prompt

## End-of-session gate

Before final reply to user:
- [ ] PROGRESS matches current ARCHITECTURE modules
- [ ] Git hash current if committed
- [ ] Recent changes has this session
- [ ] Next session is actionable
